<doc id="12345" url="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=12345" title="Demographics of Guadeloupe">
Demographics of Guadeloupe

Guadeloupe has a population of 403,977 (2012).
Population.
According to INSEE Guadeloupe has an estimated population of 403,977 on January 1, 2012. Life expectancy at birth is 77.0 years for males, and 83.5 for females (figures for 2011).
Languages.
French is the official language, taught in the school system. Antillean Creole French is spoken by a large part of the population, understood by nearly all, and taught in some schools. A 2007 document issued by the International Organization of la Francophonie estimated the population to be 80.2% "francophone" and 14.9% "partially francophone".
